Description:
Domain Precinct - Renovate or Build Your Dream Home
Occupy, renovate or build your dream home with approved plans and permit for contemporary architect designed residence.
Solid brick freestanding home on a 302sqm (approx.) allotment currently showcasing three bedroom accommodation plus study area with adjacent living room, west facing courtyard and off-street parking via ROW (Airlie Bank Lane) at rear. Featuring an open plan kitchen and family room flowing out to a North-Western courtyard, this single level home is liveable as is with scope for improvement in the future.
Alternatively, build your luxurious dream home with approved plans and permit for stunning architecturally designed residence featuring four bedrooms plus study, multiple living spaces, sunny Northern aspect and off-street parking.
Superbly located and elevated in the tightly held Domain Precinct with superb views to the North, this rare opportunity is within walking distance to the Royal Botanic Gardens, Yarra River and access to the CBD, leading schools and an array of eateries and boutique stores in the Domain Precinct.
Insights: 49 Airlie Street, South Yarra VIC 3141 was last sold in 2019 and 61 other 3 bedroom house in South Yarra have recently been sold.

Address: 88A Surrey Road North South Yarra VIC 3141
Description:
Street front independence, meters to Chapel Street
In an area filled with lifestyle benefits, this location is its draw card whilst also offering the ability to lock up and leave. Whilst many low maintenance living environments may offer this advantage, very few can provide it with the luxury of independence. On its own Title, behind its own street frontage, this two-bedroom two-bathroom townhouse not only provides this rare privilege, it does so with effortless style and secure parking just meters from Chapel Street, Toorak Road and Rockley Gardens! A generous light filled living/dining domain and fully equipped kitchen provide plenty of space to relax and entertain whilst two spacious upstairs bedrooms both with ensuites and BIRs. Ducted heating/cooling, alarm, street front entry, direct access to secure rear parking, additional permit parking. What more could you need with tranquil Surrey Park at the doorstep and Melbourne's most iconic lifestyle precinct, trams, trains, Prahran Market and more all within meters?

Description:
Renovated Victorian Primed For Lifestyle
Period elegance, modern style and a fabulous central position ensure this superbly renovated single level Victorian delivers a lifestyle to love in a quiet pocket near Chapel Street and Fawkner Park. Behind its high private fence, two gorgeous bedrooms retain their early refinement with high ceilings and ornate open fireplaces, one with built in robes/storage. Glossy timber floors continue through light filled open plan living spaces that feature a fully equipped kitchen before charming French doors reveal a landscaped northern courtyard perfect for alfresco entertaining. An immaculate bathroom with laundry facilities, ducted heating and secluded entry courtyard complete an irresistible first home, investment or downsize residence.

Description:
Modern Luxury, Panoramic Views and Complete Convenience
Showcasing a panoramic landscape spanning from Port Phillip Bay across Melbournes skyline out as far as the Macedon Ranges from floor to ceiling windows, this elevated apartment on the 23rd floor is sure to impress. Exceptional designer style, a soft neutral colour palette and a peerless level of quality are displayed throughout the floorplan which comprises of an open plan living and dining area bathed in ambient light which seamlessly integrates indoor/outdoor entertaining with the terrace balcony opening through glass sliding doors, taking in the very best of the breath-taking view. The sleek kitchen has all the extras you should expect from a home of this calibre, finished with a full complement of premium Miele appliances including an integrated dishwasher. Two sizeable bedrooms are both fitted with built in robes, a luxurious bathroom offers an oversized shower whilst a European laundry, secure basement carspace, storage cage, video intercom, heating/cooling, access to the concierge and resident only rooftop retreat with sky terrace, lounge, kitchen, dining room, gym, sauna and indoor pool are sought after highlights. Delivering superior convenience, mere footsteps from cafes and restaurants, South Yarra Station, trams and the Yarra River bike trails.

Immediate proximity to Botanic Gardens, Fawkner Park Toorak Road cafes and shops, the City, MCG and sports and entertainment precinct, Chapel Street, trams, and South Yarra Train Station.
An inspection will not disappoint.

Description:
Fully Renovated Classic Edwardian Residence
Beautifully located in a quiet cul-de-sac only a short walk to Hawksburn Village and Chapel Street, is this attractive contemporary solid brick Edwardian gem of generous proportions whilst retaining ornate features, in the heart of South Yarra.
The traditional tone is set by the charming façade followed by two double bedrooms with high ceilings, ornate fireplaces and built in robes. The exceptionally spacious lounge and dining room has high ceilings complimented by bespoke cabinetry, American Oak floorboards and double glazed bi-fold doors leading to manicured and low maintenance courtyard garden with special lighting to set the ambience, perfect for entertaining. The bright open plan modern kitchen has Corian bench tops, integrated fridge, Miele appliances, ample cupboard space and opening onto side outdoor meals area. The sparkling central bathroom is stunning with standalone bathtub and floor to ceiling imported tiling. Other features include integrated heating and cooling, European laundry, plantation shutters, doggy door at the rear and most important, off-street parking to conclude this special home.
This convenient position is a short walk to Hawksburn and South Yarra trendy restaurant & cafe precinct, vibrant Chapel Street shopping, Hawksburn station, trams, Surrey Park, Prahran Market, Schools and within ten minutes of the CBD.
INSPECT AS ADVERTSED OR BY APPOINTMENT

Description:
Spacious Ground-Floor Lavishness in Ultimate Locale!
The solid and proudly-maintained, boutique block enjoys alternative access via a quiet side street and exceptional, camera security. The apartment comes with a secure car park. Ground level, stair-free and ready to a lock-up-and-leave as desired, it offers elegant ease fit for all ages and stages of life.
Classically styled and splendidly appointed, this magnificent apartment pairs a super-spacious interior with a large courtyard for effortless, formal and casual entertaining and gracious, indoor/outdoor living.
Enter to a hall announcing a laundry; regal, black-and-white kitchen with granite benchtops, Miele appliances and broad, shuttered servery to the dining room; dining room open to large living room with french doors to paved, private and leafy, 35-square-metre courtyard.
Side hallway accesses a beautiful, marble bathroom with twin vanity, shower and bath; big second bedroom with built-in wardrobes and massive main bedroom with walk-in wardrobe.
A semi, open-plan flow, high ceilings, fresh carpets and ducted heating reinforce comfort and immaculate presentation, while the courtyard encourages al-fresco relaxation, sociable barbecues and exercising green thumbs.
With trams passing the door and trains and buses in easy reach, Rockley Gardens and the South Yarra Library steps away and restaurants galore in walking distance, the cosmopolitan location guarantees enduring prestige and exceptional convenience in an environment ideal for busy executives, active couples and discerning downsizers alike.
You can shop up a storm and go bar-hopping on Chapel Street, or settle in for a lush night at home, confident in a rewarding investment in your own slice of South Yarra paradise.
Taking your luxurious lifestyle to new levels, call Paul Torok on 0490815564 to secure your must-see inspection.
Internal area
105m²

Description:
Pure South Yarra Pleasure
INSPECT STRICTLY BY APPOINTMENT
The beauty of possessing an address in the Royal Botanic Gardens precinct is perfectly expressed by this refined residence over two floors, a property where superb indoor proportions are matched by inviting outdoor dimensions including a majestic roof-top terrace featuring a swimming pool and fabulous city views. Memorably updated and enhanced under the assured guidance of Stuart Rattle, the design delivers separate formal and informal living and dining domains, each accompanied by private courtyard that provide perfect retreats for entertaining in style or simply enjoying a sense of escape. An open-plan kitchen complemented by oak flooring, stone surfaces, a central island and a walk-in pantry caters to any occasion with efficiency and elegance while a versatile study adds to the downstairs attraction. Upstairs, balcony aspects and terrace access enhance the luxury of a main bedroom featuring a generous walk-in robe and a substantial spa bath ensuite. Two further bedrooms, both with built-in robes, share an impressively appointed main bathroom that confirms the quality of the accommodation. The pool's paved surroundings and the sights of the city take the allure to the next level, creating a sensational conclusion to a home offering the consummate convenience of double garage and additional off street parking for two. Leading schools, Domain Road cafes, the 'tan' track, Fawkner Park, the Yarra and Toorak Road ensure there are attractions in literally every direction - What a great location!

Description:
Entry Level in Blue Chip Suburb
Take advantage of this modern studio apartment just moments away from the iconic Chapel Street. It is perfect for the budding first home buyer looking to get a foothold in the property market or the opportunistic investor that knows value.
Enjoy the much desired South Yarra lifestyle with everything only a stone's throw away including: the Como Centre, Vogue Plaza, Rockley Gardens, South Yarra Library, the Yarra River trails and the myriad of restaurants, cafes and boutique shops along Toorak Road and Chapel Street.
Providing what you need to live comfortably this compact space is action packed with a modern bathroom, Euro laundry and galley kitchen with gas cook top and oven. The fold-up bed gives you options to open up the living space when desired with ample storage built in on either side. The living area is open and connects the generous east facing balcony which enjoys the morning sun.
The building houses: Security intercom, business centre, gym, resident's garden, outdoor terrace, 2 x rooftop spa's, rooftop cinema, lounge area and kitchen.

Description:
Classic Charm, Contemporary Renovation
Offering the very best of inner city living, this cleverly re-designed, charming semi-detached Victorian terrace delivers the ideal first home or downsizer. Period character combines with a brilliant renovation showcasing outstanding contemporary living filled with natural light. The easy flowing floorplan and modern ambience provide a fabulous feel for year-round relaxing and entertaining. Directly opposite a secure childrens playground, walk to schools, South Yarra and Prahran Stations, trams, Prahran Market, shops, dining and nightlife on Chapel Street, Toorak and Commercial Roads.

Victorian Charm in the Domain Precinct
This classic free standing double fronted Hawthorn brick Victorian residence enjoys a prized Domain Precinct location between Fawkner Park and the Botanic Gardens and offers immediate lifestyle and investment rewards, along with exceptional scope to update and extend in the future (STCA).
Displaying period features including Baltic pine floors and high ceilings, the central arched hall flows through to an inviting living room with open fire, well appointed separate timber kitchen and a light-filled dining room. Every lifestyle amenity is at your doorstep, whilst this entertainers dream boasts privacy and seclusion. Walk down a long leafy path to discover this superb, low-maintenance single-level oasis hidden away within Melbourne's most iconic retail and restaurant precinct.
